{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01EbK2s3L8gwra8giqpDb3Z9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to generate 10 realistic fake OCR recipe text files. Let me break down the requirements:\n\n1. **FILENAME RULES**:\n   - Use SPACES, not hyphens or underscores\n   - Format: `{RECIPE_TITLE}.generated.18.txt`\n   - Preserve Polish diacritics\n   - Title must match content (case-insensitive OK)\n   - Save to: `tools/title-loop/input/`\n\n2. **RECIPE MIX**:\n   - ~60% English, ~40% Polish\n   - Variety of categories: soups, mains, desserts, salads, appetizers, breads, drinks, preserves\n   - Mix of single-word and multi-word titles (2-5 words)\n   - Must NOT use the ~150+ existing recipes listed\n\n3. **PATTERN REQUIREMENTS** (10 files total):\n   - 5 files: SIMPLE (basic OCR noise, stray numbers, page headers, broken words)\n   - 3 files: OCR_CORRUPTION (misrecognized characters, e.g., 'só1' for 'sól', 'ı' for 'l')\n   - 2 files: NARRATIVE (3-7 lines of prose intro before ingredient list)\n\n4. **FILE LENGTH**: 15-60 lines\n\nLet me plan my 10 recipes:\n- English (6-7): Carrot Soup, Vanilla Cake, Green Pesto, Potato Salad, Mushroom Risotto, Blackberry Jam, Herb Butter\n- Polish (3-4): Kompot Brzoskwiniowy, Placki Tradycyjne, Zupa Grochowa, Piekarnik Wielkanocny\n\nWait, I need to check the exclusion list more carefully. Let me identify recipes that are NOT in the list:\n\nLooking at the exclusion list, I can see recipes like:\n\n\n- Apple Crumble, Apple Pie, Appple Pie Salad, Caesar Salad, etc.\n\nLet me create 10 NEW recipes that avoid these:\n\n1. **Carrot Soup** (English, SIMPLE)\n2. **Placki Tradycyjne** (Polish, SIMPLE)\n3. **Vanilla Cake** (English, OCR_CORRUPTION)\n4. **Zupa Grochowa** (Polish, OCR_CORRUPTION)\n5. **Green Pesto** (English, NARRATIVE)\n6. **Kompot Brzoskwiniowy** (Polish, SIMPLE)\n7. **Potato Salad** (English, SIMPLE)\n8. **Mushroom Risotto** (English, OCR_CORRUPTION)\n9. **Blackberry Jam** (Polish, NARRATIVE)\n10. **Herb Butter** (English, NARRATIVE)\n\nLet me verify these aren't duplicates. Checking against existing recipes: \"Carrot Ginger Soup\" and \"Carrot Turnip Soup\" exist but not plain \"Carrot Soup\". \"Potato Salad\" isn't in the current collection. \"Mushroom Risotto\" differs from the asparagus and tomato variants already listed. \"Green Pesto\" is absent. \"Blackberry Jam\" is distinct from \"Berry Jam\" and the Polish berry preserve. \"Vanilla Cake\" is new despite \"Chocolate Cake\" being present. These selections should work without overlap. - not in list\n2. **Cucumber Salad** (English, SIMPLE) - various salads are listed like Greek, Caesar, Kale, Caprese, and Mizeria, but none match this exactly\n3. **Raspberry Cheesecake** (English, OCR_CORRUPTION) - Cheesecake and Blueberry Cheesecake appear in the exclusion list, but this specific variant doesn't\n4. **Zupa Pi\n\n**eczarkowa** (Polish, OCR_CORRUPTION) - Mushroom Barley Soup and Zupa Grzybowa are present, though not this particular mushroom soup variant\n5. **Lemon Bars** (English, NARRATIVE) - Lemon-based desserts and dishes exist (Meringue Pie, Risotto, Pound Cake) but this one isn't among them\n6. **Kompot Brzoskwiniowy** (Polish, SIMPLE) - absent from the list\n7. **Herb Butter** (English, OCR_CORRUPTION) - not found\n8. **Mushroom Pasta** (English, SIMPLE) - mushroom dishes like Stroganoff and Polenta with Wild Mushrooms are listed, along with Spaghetti Carbonara, yet this pasta dish isn't included\n9. **Malinowiec**\n\n(Polish, NARRATIVE) - missing from the list\n10. **Walnut Bread** (English, SIMPLE) - various breads appear (Sourdough, Irish Soda, Ciabatta, Garlic, Focaccia, Rosemary Olive Oil, Pita) but Walnut Bread is not among them\n\nThe files are organized by pattern type: SIMPLE includes basic OCR noise and formatting artifacts (files 1, 2, 6, 8, 10), OCR_CORRUPTION features character misrecognition (files 3, 4, 7), and NARRATIVE contains prose introductions (files 5, 9). Now generating the ten files with these patterns applied.\n\nInstructions continue with heating oil, sautéing aromatics for 3-4 minutes, adding carrots and broth to simmer for 15 minutes until tender, blending smooth, stirring in coconut milk, seasoning, and garnishing with thyme. The recipe yields 4 servings with 10 minutes prep and 20 minutes cooking time.\n\nFor the second file, Cucumber Salad includes thinly sliced cucumbers, white vinegar, sugar, red onion, and fresh dill. The method combines vinegar and sugar until dissolved, tosses with cucumbers and onion, seasons with salt, pepper and dill, then refrigerates.\n\nThe third recipe shows OCR corruption issues with misspelled words like \"RASРBERRY\" and \"Crսst\" throughout. The cheesecake has three components: a graham cracker crust mixed with butter and sugar pressed into a pan, a filling of softened cream cheese beaten with sugar, eggs, vanilla and raspberries, and a topping of sour cream with honey. Instructions begin with mixing and pressing the crust, then beating cream cheese and sugar until fluffy. ymianek to garnish. Heat oil in a pot and sauté the onion and garlic until softened, about 3-4 minutes. Add mushrooms and broth, bring to a boil, then simmer for 15 minutes. Use an immersion blender to puree the soup. Stir in cream and season with salt and pepper. Serve hot, garnished with fresh thyme. Yields 4 servings.\n\nPrep time is 10 minutes. Moving on to lemon bars—a spring dessert inspired by my grandmother's Tuscan garden. She'd harvest fresh lemons and create these bars with their bright, tangy flavor. The buttery shortbread base pairs beautifully with the silky lemon custard layer, making them ideal for afternoon tea or as a light finish to dinner. The shortbread crust requires flour, powdered sugar, cold butter, and salt, while the filling combines eggs, sugar, flour, and lemon juice. ns fresh basil, chopped\n1 tablespoon fresh thyme leaves\n3 cloves garlic, minced\n1/2 teaspoon sea salt\n1/4 teaspoon black pepper\nZest of 1 lemon\n\nInstructions:\n1. Combine all herbs and garlic in a bowl.\n2. Beat butter until creamy, then fold in herb mixture.\n3. Shape into log using plastic wrap.\n4. Refrigerate for at least 2 hours before slicing.\n5. Use on steaks, vegetables, or bread.\n\nYield: 1 cup\n\n### 8. Mushroom Pasta (SIMPLE, 20 lines)\n\nMUSHROOM PASTA\n\nPage 234\n\nIngredients:\n400 g fresh pasta\n500 g mixed mushrooms, sliced\n4 cloves garlic, minced\n1/2 cup dry white wine\n1/2 cup heavy cream\n2 tablespoons butter\nFresh parsley, chopped\nParmesan cheese, grated\nSalt and pepper\n\nMethod:\n1. Cook pasta in salted boiling water until al dente.\n2. Sauté mushrooms in butter until golden, about 5-7 minutes.\n3. Add garlic and cook for 1 minute until fragrant.\n4. Deglaze pan with white wine, reduce by half.\n5. Add cream and simmer gently for 3-4 minutes.\n6. Toss cooked pasta with mushroom sauce.\n7. Season with salt and pepper, top with parsley and Parmesan.\n\nServings: 4\n\n### 9. Malinowiec (NARRATIVE, 38 lines)\n\nMALINOWIEC\n\nW każde lato, kiedy przychodziła pora zbiorów malin, nasza babcia przygotowywała to wspani ałe ciasto. Malinowiec to tradycyjne ciasto drożdżowe z malinami z Podlasia, znane z aromatycznej, miękkiej struktury i słodkiej mąki, które zawsze robiły wrażenie na gościach. Najlepsze podawane świeże z herbatą.\n\nCiasto Drożdżowe:\n500 g mąki pszennej\n250 ml mleka, letniego\n50 g drożdży świeżych\n100 g masła\n2 żółtka\n1 łyżeczka soli\n50 g cukru\n\nNadzienie:\n600 g świeżych malin\n100 g cukru\n2 łyżki mąki\n\nPrzygotowanie:\n1.\n\nRozpuszcz drożdże w ciepłym mleku z cukrem. Wymieszaj mąkę i sól, uformuj dołek pośrodku, wlej mieszankę drożdżową, dodaj żółtka i masło, następnie wyrabiaj przez 10 minut aż ciasto stanie się elastyczne. Postaw do wyrośnięcia przez godzinę, rozłóż na blasze, przykryj malinami, pospryskaj cukrem i mąką, piecz w 180°C przez 35-40 minut aż się złoci.\n\nPorcje: 10-12\n\nChleb orzechowy wymaga połączenia mąki, soli i drożdży, następnie dodania ciepłej wody z miodem i wyrobienia przez 10 minut. Po włączeniu posiekanych orzechów ciasto wyrasta przez 1-2 godziny, formuje się w bochnek, nacina się nożem i piecze w 425°F przez 35-40 minut aż będzie złoty i wydawać będzie pusty dźwięk.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":14930,"cache_read_input_tokens":65286,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":14930},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"508918cb-2cda-4253-a72b-01239bf6ad27","uuid":"56e90066-7cd9-469f-b305-da51a1413c4e"}
