{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01EbK2s3L8gwra8giqpDb3Z9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01AW1UgnyS59FR7WXyoupGQ1","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Lemon Bars.generated.18.txt","content":"LEMON BARS\n\nEvery spring, my grandmother would gather lemons from her garden in Tuscany\nand transform them into these vibrant, tangy lemon bars. The combination of a\nbuttery shortbread crust and a silky lemon custard filling became a family\ntradition passed down through generations. These bars are perfect for afternoon\ntea or as a refreshing dessert after a heavy meal. The bright citrus flavor\nawakens the palate beautifully.\n\nShortbread Crust:\n2 cups all-purpose flour\n1/2 cup powdered sugar\n1 cup cold butter, cubed\nPinch of salt\n\nLemon Filling:\n4 eggs\n1 1/2 cups sugar\n3 tablespoons all-purpose flour\n1/4 teaspoon baking powder\n1/2 cup fresh lemon juice\nZest of 2 lemons\n\nInstructions:\n1. Prepare crust: mix flour, sugar, and salt. Cut in cold\n   butter until crumbly. Press into greased 9x13 pan.\n2. Bake crust at 350°F for 12-15 minutes until golden.\n3. For filling: whisk eggs and sugar until light. Fold in\n   flour, baking powder, lemon juice, and zest.\n4. Pour over crust and bake at 350°F for 20-25 minutes\n   until set and edges are light brown.\n5. Cool completely, dust with powdered sugar, and cut into\n   bars.\n\nServings: 16\nDifficulty: Easy\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":14930,"cache_read_input_tokens":65286,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":14930},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"508918cb-2cda-4253-a72b-01239bf6ad27","uuid":"d6c6b1ea-afc2-45a3-8f2b-faa215ed5660"}
